image.altText: David Warner and Usman Khawaja run past each other

items.synopsis: Australia need 281 runs to win the first Ashes Test at Edgbaston after England went on the attack with the bat on day four. Follow live.

title.children: Australian openers weather early near misses as they chase 281 to win first Ashes Test

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Well that was frustrating for Australia, but importantly for England, the last three wickets added 63 runs, which could be the difference in this match. Wow. More questions have to be asked about Australia's inability to bowl out the tail. Also, where was Cameron Green? And that's tea, so Australia should have 42 overs in this final session. The Aussies have plenty of time. They need to knuckle down because otherwise they could easily be five wickets down at stumps. There's supposed to be a bit of rain tomorrow, so I'd say it's easier for Australia to lose the Test in this session than to win it, but let's see how they go.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Jimmy Anderson nicks off and Australia needs 281 runs to win

The Aussies have plenty of time. They need to knuckle down because otherwise they could easily be five wickets down at stumps.
There's supposed to be a bit of rain tomorrow, so I'd say it's easier for Australia to lose the Test in this session than to win it, but let's see how they go.

image.altText: Albanese stands speaking to media from a courtyard.

title.children: Federal government a step closer to early election trigger as Senate rejects housing bill

image.altText: The bow of the RMS Titanic.

items.synopsis: A search is underway for a submersible craft that is missing near the wreck on the TItanic.

title.children: The nurse in the COVID outbreak unit who had to resign after wetting herself in PPE

image.altText: An Aboriginal flag in the foreground, Parliament House in the background

title.children: Referendum legislation passes parliament, putting Australia on track for Voice vote

image.altText: Fire crews stand in front of an overturned bus beside a road.

image.altText: Aleh Sidorchyk smokes a cigarette as he walks out of the Adelaide city police watch house.

title.children: Actor who indecently touched female passenger on flight to Australia fined $750 but not jailed

image.altText: Kitchen Hut, Cradle Mountain, Tasmania.

title.children: Nick Kyrgios out of Halle with knee injury but still hopes to play Wimbledon
